'''Esmir Bajraktarević''' ({{IPA|bs|ěsmir bajraktâːreʋitɕ|pron}}; born 10 March 2005) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]] for [[Eredivisie]] club [[PSV Eindhoven|PSV]]. Born in the United States, he plays for the [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina national team]].

Bajraktarević started his professional career at [[New England Revolution]], playing first in its [[New England Revolution II|reserve team]]. He signed for Dutch club PSV in 2025, where he won the Eredivisie title in his debut season.

A former American youth international, Bajraktarević also made his senior international debut for the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]], before switching his allegiance to Bosnia and Herzegovina in 2024, earning 16 [[Cap (sport)|caps]] since.

==Club career==

===New England Revolution===
Bajraktarević started playing football at a local club SC Wave, before joining [[Chicago Fire FC|Chicago Fire's youth setup]] in 2019. The following year, he returned to SC Wave. A year later, he switched to [[New England Revolution|New England Revolution's youth academy]]. In May 2022, he signed his first professional contract with the team. He made his professional debut playing for [[New England Revolution II|New England Revolution's reserve squad]] against [[Tormenta FC]] on 22 August 2021 at the age of 16. On 11 September, he scored his first professional goal against [[North Carolina FC]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://soccerwire.com/news/new-england-revolution-sign-17-year-old-esmir-bajraktarevic-as-homegrown-player|title=New England Revolution sign 17-year-old Esmir Bajraktarević as Homegrown Player|website=soccerwire.com|date=23 May 2022|access-date=26 May 2022}}</ref>

Bajraktarević made his first-team debut in a [[2022 U.S. Open Cup#Round of 16|U.S. Open Cup]] game against [[New York City FC]] on 26 May 2022. Three months later, he made his league debut against [[Toronto FC]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://theblazingmusket.com/the-story-of-esmir-bajraktarevic-a-rising-star-in-american-soccer|title=The story of Esmir Bajraktarevic, a rising star in American soccer|website=theblazingmusket.com|date=12 February 2024|access-date=13 February 2024}}</ref> On 8 August 2023, he scored his first goal for New England Revolution in a [[2023 Leagues Cup#Round of 16|Leagues Cup]] match against [[Querétaro F.C.|Querétaro]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://masslive.com/sports/2023/08/esmir-bajraktarevic-nets-first-goal-but-revolution-fall-in-pks-during-leagues-cup.html|title=Esmir Bajraktarevic nets first goal, but Revolution fall in PKs during Leagues Cup|website=masslive.com|date=8 August 2023|access-date=11 August 2023}}</ref> Ten months later, he scored his first league goal for the side in a triumph over [[Nashville SC]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://masslive.com/sports/2024/06/esmir-bajraktarevic-scores-first-goal-to-help-revolution-snap-nashvilles-shutout-streak.html|title=Esmir Bajraktarevic scores first goal to help Revolution snap Nashville's shutout streak|website=masslive.com|date=1 June 2024|access-date=1 June 2024}}</ref>

===PSV===
In January 2025, Bajraktarević was transferred to Dutch outfit [[PSV Eindhoven|PSV]] for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://fokus.ba/sport/fudbal/esmir-bajraktarevic-potpisao-za-psv-eindhoven-jedva-cekam-da-zaigram-za-legendarni-klub/3393007|title=Esmir Bajraktarević potpisao za PSV Eindhoven: Jedva čekam da zaigram za legendarni klub|website=fokus.ba|date=2 January 2025|access-date=3 January 2025|language=bs}}</ref> On 18 January, he made his official debut for the squad against [[PEC Zwolle|Zwolle]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://radiosarajevo.ba/sport/nogomet/prvi-nastup-mlade-nade-bh-nogometa-esmir-bajraktarevic-debitirao-za-psv-eindhoven/575597|title=Prvi nastup mlade nade bh. nogometa: Esmir Bajraktarević debitirao za PSV Eindhoven|website=radiosarajevo.ba|date=18 January 2025|access-date=19 January 2025|language=bs}}</ref> Bajraktarević debuted in the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League#Round of 16|UEFA Champions League]] away at [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] on 12 March.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://klix.ba/sport/nogomet/arsenal-i-aston-villa-spasili-cast-engleza-bajraktarevic-debitovao-u-ligi-prvaka/250312204|title=Arsenal i Aston Villa spasili čast Engleza, Bajraktarević debitovao u Ligi prvaka|website=klix.ba|date=12 March 2025|access-date=14 March 2025|language=bs}}</ref> He won his first trophy with the club on 18 May, when they were crowned league champions.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://n1info.ba/sport/nogomet/psv-odbranio-naslov-prvaka-nizozemske-esmir-bajraktarevic-slavio-prvi-veliki-trofej-u-karijeri|title=PSV odbranio naslov prvaka Nizozemske: Esmir Bajraktarević slavio prvi veliki trofej u karijeri|website=n1info.ba|date=18 May 2025|access-date=19 May 2025|language=bs}}</ref> On 23 August, he scored a brace in a defeat of [[FC Groningen|Groningen]], which were his first goals for PSV.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://avaz.ba/sport/nogomet/992482/bajraktarevic-zablistao-dva-gola-za-psv-i-jasna-poruka-barbarezu|title=Bajraktarević zablistao: Dva gola za PSV i jasna poruka Barbarezu|website=avaz.ba|date=23 August 2025|access-date=26 August 2025|language=bs}}</ref>

==International career==
After representing the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]] at various youth levels, Bajraktarević made his senior international debut in a [[Exhibition game#Association football|friendly]] game against [[Slovenia national football team|Slovenia]] on 20 January 2024. However, in July, he decided that he would play for [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]] in the future.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://faktor.ba/sport/fudbal/esmir-bajraktarevic-poslao-jasnu-poruku-amerikancima-jako-sam-ponosan-sto-sam-bosanac/192201|title=Esmir Bajraktarević poslao jasnu poruku Amerikancima: Jako sam ponosan što sam Bosanac|website=faktor.ba|date=4 July 2024|access-date=6 July 2024|language=bs}}</ref>

In August, his request to change sports citizenship from American to Bosnian was approved by [[FIFA]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://radiosarajevo.ba/sport/nogomet/spahic-otkrio-kako-su-zmajevi-ukrali-jednu-veliku-nogometnu-nadu-i-privoljeli-ga-da-igra-za-bih/557289|title=Spahić otkrio kako su Zmajevi "ukrali" jednu veliku nogometnu nadu i privoljeli ga da igra za BiH|website=radiosarajevo.ba|date=16 August 2024|access-date=19 August 2024|language=bs}}</ref> Later that month, he received his first senior call up, for [[2024–25 UEFA Nations League A#Group 3|2024–25 UEFA Nations League A]] matches against the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] and [[Hungary national football team|Hungary]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/435895-barbarez-je-promijenio-spisak-u-odnosu-na-englesku-i-italiju-na-raspolaganju-je-sedam-novih-imena|title=Barbarez je promijenio spisak u odnosu na Englesku i Italiju, na raspolaganju je sedam novih imena|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=16 August 2024|access-date=19 August 2024|language=bs}}</ref> He debuted against the former on 7 September.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://fokus.ba/sport/fudbal/slabasna-bih-primila-pet-golova-od-nizozemske-bajraktarevic-jedini-svijetla-tacka/3333359|title=Slabašna BiH primila pet golova od Nizozemske, Bajraktarević jedini svijetla tačka|website=fokus.ba|date=7 September 2024|access-date=9 September 2024|language=bs}}</ref>

On 15 November 2025, in a [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA Group H|2026 FIFA World Cup qualifier]] against [[Romania national football team|Romania]], he scored his first senior international goal.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://avaz.ba/sport/nogomet/1006817/zmajevi-slavili-nakon-preokreta-u-zenici-i-osigurali-minimalno-baraz-za-direktan-plasman-na-sp-potrebna-pobjeda-u-becu|title=Zmajevi slavili nakon preokreta u Zenici i osigurali minimalno baraž: Za direktan plasman na SP potrebna pobjeda u Beču|website=avaz.ba|date=15 November 2025|access-date=16 November 2025|language=bs}}</ref> On 31 March 2026, he scored the winning [[Penalty kick (association football)|penalty]] in a [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shoot-out]] against [[Italy national football team|Italy]] in the [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA second round|UEFA World Cup qualifying playoffs]] to send Bosnia and Herzegovina to the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/european-qualifiers/news/02a3-2047c06e29c6-0a8f1c84272a-1000--bosnia-and-herzegovina-1-1-italy-4-3-on-pens-hosts-win-2026/ |title=Bosnia and Herzegovina 1-1 Italy highlights (4-3 on pens): Hosts win 2026 World Cup play-off final shoot-out |publisher=UEFA |date=31 March 2026 }}</ref>

In June 2026, Bajraktarević was named in Bosnia and Herzegovina's squad for the 2026 World Cup.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportske.ba/clanak/barbarez-poslao-konacan-spisak-fifa-i-jedno-ime-otputovalo-u-ameriku-ali-nije-na-listi|title=Barbarez poslao konačan spisak FIFA-i: Jedno ime otputovalo u Ameriku, ali nije na listi|website=sportske.ba|date=3 June 2026|access-date=3 June 2026|language=bs}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Bajraktarević's parents, Elmir and Emina, were both born in [[Srebrenica]]. They survived the [[Srebrenica genocide]] in 1995, during which Bajraktarević's maternal grandfather, four uncles, and several other relatives were killed.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Portal |first=Valter |date=2025-11-17 |title=PORIJEKLOM IZ SREBRENICE: Ko je Esmir Barjaktarević? |url=https://valterportal.ba/porijeklom-iz-srebrenice-ko-je-esmir-barjaktarevic/ |access-date=2026-06-06 |website=Valter Portal |language=bs-BA}}</ref> Following the [[Bosnian War]], the family spent some time as refugees in [[Switzerland]] before emigrating to the [[United States]] in 2001.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-04-01 |title='Milwaukee Messi' odveo BiH na SP. Roditelji pobjegli iz pakla Srebrenice, a mentor mu Perišić |url=https://www.24sata.hr/sport/milwaukee-messi-odveo-bih-na-sp-roditelji-pobjegli-iz-pakla-srebrenice-a-mentor-mu-perisic-1118620 |access-date=2026-06-06 |website=www.24sata.hr |language=hr}}</ref>

Esmir is the youngest of three children, with an older brother, Osman, and an older sister, Elma.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-09-10 |title=Priča o Esmiru Bajraktareviću: Uspon mladića u američkom nogometu |url=https://ntv.ba/87prica-o-esmiru-bajraktarevicu-uspon-mladica-u-americkom-nogometu/ |access-date=2026-06-06 |website=NEON Televizija |language=bs-BA}}</ref>

